      "writtenOn": "2026-06-10T10:09:03Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I tried moving this onto BuiltinValidator (a noSelfValidator constructor plus an evalEarly method on the validator), but it just spread the logic across three locations without making it clearer, so I\u0027ve kept the original.\n\nIt\u0027s consistent with how matchN/matchIf are modeled — those are also *adt.Builtin, and a *BuiltinValidator is the applied form. This block handles the first call of a no-self validator (existsN/validN/concreteN): there\u0027s no \"self\" argument, so we evaluate eagerly to surface a permanent error and otherwise return the BuiltinValidator that gets applied during validation.",
